properties.areaDesc: Tulare County; Eastern Kern County; Fort Tejon; Bakersfield; Southern Sierra Foothills
properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 27 at 5:47AM PST until January 27 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibility less than 1/4 mile and as low as a few
hundred feet in some locations.

* WHERE...The San Joaquin Valley and adjacent foothills in Tulare
county and the south end of the San Joaquin valley and north and
west facing slopes of the Kern County mountains.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility
along with travel delays.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Roads impacted by dense fog include Highway
65, Highway 198 east of Visalia, Highway 190 from Springville to
just west of Porterville and many roads in the Bakersfield area.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance between your vehicle and the vehicle in front of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING
